#2). Write a program in Python to check whether an integer is Armstrong number or not.

n=11111
i=0
b=n
c=n
result=0

while n!=0:
	n=n//10
	i=i+1

while c!=0:
	d = c % 10
	result = result + pow(d,i)
	c = c//10
    
if result == b:
	print("number is armstrong")
else:
	print("number is not armstrong")
